The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Lucknow, March 18 (PTI): Rights of Muslim women, especially in matters of inheritance and education, will be high on the agenda of the annual general conference of All India Muslim Personal Law Board, to be held here from tomorrow.           
	The three-day meeting will discuss ways to make Muslim women aware of their property rights and spread education, a member of the board said. It would also deliberate on how to set up dar-ul qaza (Islamic courts) in all the towns of Uttar Pradesh. Recent court decisions, which are against Islamic law, will also be taken up at the meeting.                  
	 Warangal (PTI): A Maoist couple, who were active in Maharashtra, surrendered in neighbouring Andhra Pradeshs Warangal district on Thursday. Mallesh and Chaya used to transport arms and propagate Maoist ideology in the 1990s, police said.                  
	 Bijnor (PTI): Three pilgrims were killed and 25 injured when their bus was hit by a lorry at a village in Uttar Pradesh, police said. Eleven of them were later sent to Meerut in a critical condition. The truck driver has been arrested.                  
	 Ferozepur (PTI): Security forces in Punjab have foiled an attempt by Pakistani agents to push a consignment of drugs and fake currency to the Indian side and killed an intruder in the exchange of fire. Fake currency with a face value of Rs18 lakh and 26 kg heroin were recovered from them, an official said. A protest will be lodged with the Pakistani Rangers.                  
	 Melbourne (PTI): Sitar legend Pandit Ravi Shankar will be honoured by the University of Melbourne with its highest award, the Doctorate Degree of Laws, for his outstanding commitment to music and humanity, a university statement said.                   
	 Kanpur (PTI): A policeman in Maharashtra was arrested for strangling a person to death after detaining him in a narcotics smuggling case.                                                                                                                                              
